 all Master Looting situations.<br>
<br>
Fear/Hate Raids-<br>
<br>
*At check-in, all raiders will provide the Master Looter with what pieces they currently have. Have all your planar on you, as we reserve the right to check.<br>
*All class-loot will be rolled to those who do not have.<br>
*Once you have received a piece, you are out of rolls until all those in your class have received an armour piece.<br>
*When everyone has received a piece, the next item will be randomed to everyone in the class.<br>
*We will honor the last piece rule.<br>
*All non-armour drops will be randomed on a &quot;will use&quot; basis and separate from the armour rolls.<br>
*All old and new god loot will be randomed seprately from other drops and on a 'will us' basis.<br>
*We reserve the right to award epic drops to those who are either far enough along on their epic to utilize this item, or those who have performed in an outstanding manner.<br>
*Cash loot and Gems will go to reimburse for Raid costs or awarded to those who have performed in an outstanding manner.<br>
<br>
Other Raids-<br>
<br>
*All items will be randomed on a &quot;will use&quot; basis<br>
*All spells will be randomed to those who &quot;can scribe&quot; first.<br>
*We reserve the right to vault or sell any item that cannot be used by anyone in attendance.<br>
*We reserve the right to award epic drops to those who are deserved.<br>
<br>
These rules are not set in stone.  These rules are merely a guide to assist us in fairly distributing loot in an orderly fashion.  All loot situations are at the Master Looter's discretion.  We have faith that he or she will come to a fair and quick decision in all loot matters.<br>
<br>
If you have any problems with the way in which loot has been awarded, please speak with the Master Looter.  If you cannot come to an understanding with him/her, speak with a guild officer at the end of the raid.<br>
